==Notes==

*'''A''' {{Note|note_a1}} One of the first physical singles that was certified with levels of ''Gold=5,000 and Platinum=10,000'' was "[[A Moment Like This]]" by [[Kelly Clarkson]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cria.ca/gold/0403_g.php |title=Gold & Platinum Certifications: April 2003 |work=CRIA |accessdate=2015-12-26 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106090017/http://www.cria.ca/gold/0403_g.php |archivedate=November 6, 2012 }}</ref> which was released on September 17, 2002.
*'''B''' {{Note|note_b1}} One of the first digital singles that was certified with levels of ''Gold=20,000 and Platinum=40,000'' was "[[Paralyzer]]" by [[Finger Eleven]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cria.ca/gold/0807_g.php |title=Gold & Platinum Certifications: August 2007 |work=CRIA |accessdate=2015-12-26 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120407085353/http://www.cria.ca/gold/0807_g.php |archivedate=April 7, 2012 }}</ref> which was released as a digital track on March 6, 2007.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.amazon.com/Paralyzer/dp/B002ZBFBJ2/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1340562557&s=dmusic&sr=1-1|title=Amazon: Paralyzer|publisher=[[Amazon.com]]|accessdate=2012-06-24}}</ref>
*'''C''' {{Note|note_c1}} One of the first digital singles that was certified with levels of ''Gold=40,000 and Platinum=80,000'' was "[[OMG (Usher song)|OMG]]" by [[Usher (entertainer)|Usher]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cria.ca/gold/0610_g.php |title=Gold & Platinum Certifications: June 20107 |work=CRIA |accessdate=2015-12-26 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140212153744/http://www.cria.ca/gold/0610_g.php |archivedate=February 12, 2014 }}</ref> which was released as a digital track on March 30, 2010.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.amazon.com/OMG/dp/B003DEE470/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1340561579&s=dmusic&sr=1-1|title=Amazon: OMG|publisher=[[Amazon.com]]|accessdate=2012-06-24}}</ref>

